## The Dental Equipment Leasing Trap

### The Hidden Cost of Leasing Dental Equipment

Dr. Michael runs a dental clinic in Mont Kiara. He was paying RM 15,000 monthly to lease 2 dental chairs, digital X-ray, and sterilization equipment. After 36 months, he'd paid RM 540,000 in lease fees.

**For that same amount, he could have owned all equipment plus a CAD/CAM system.**

But the dental equipment leasing company made it seem convenient: "No maintenance worries, no down payment, just pay monthly."

What they didn't tell him:

- He built zero equity despite paying RM 540,000
- Every patient treatment was reduced in profit by lease costs
- His practice couldn't add advanced procedures without more leased equipment
- Equipment upgrades required new lease agreements at higher rates

### The Treatment Limitation Problem

**Leased equipment controls your practice capabilities, not the other way around.**

- Need emergency dental procedures after hours? "Equipment service is business hours only."
- Want to add cosmetic dentistry services? "Requires additional specialized equipment lease."
- Equipment fails during peak patient hours? "Technician will be available tomorrow."

**When you don't own your dental equipment, you don't control your treatment offerings.**

